{
  "texts": [
    "Legal experts should be proactively engaged alongside scientists and ethicists to evaluate where existing laws are insufficient.",
    "The potential for unprecedented applications warrants an evolving governance approach responsive to ongoing legal gaps.",
    "A flexible but principled legal foundation for organoid research can help realize benefits ethically.",
    "The ethical discussions summarized so far might need to be translated into regulation and governance.",
    "A special status beyond other types of organoids would result from possibly achieving consciousness."
  ]
}